 u = \frac{2x}{x^2 + y^2} = \frac{2 \cos \theta}{r} 
 v = \frac{-2y}{x^2 + y^2} = \frac{- 2 \sin \theta}{r} 
 \tan \theta = - \frac{v}{u} \Rightarrow \theta = \tan^{-1} \left(-\frac{v}{u}\right), 
 u^2 + v^2 = \frac{4}{r^2} \Rightarrow r = \frac{2}{\sqrt{u^2+v^2}}. 
